				},
				"description": "**Login API**\n\nThis is a **POST API** used for user login. The request body must include the following two parameters:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"moderator_name\": \"user002\",\n  \"moderator_region_id\": 2\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Parameters**\n\n- `moderator_name` _(string)_ – The name/identifier of the moderator.\n    \n- `moderator_region_id` _(integer)_ – The region ID associated with the moderator.\n    \n\n**Response**\n\nUpon successful authentication, the API returns an **access token**. This token must be included in subsequent API requests to authenticate and authorize the user."
			},
			"response": []
		},
		{
			"name": "All Events",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {\r",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
							"});\r",
							"\r",
							"let response = pm.response.json();\r",
							"\r",
							"/* Check response schema */\r",
							"pm.test(\"Response has required fields\", function () {\r",
							"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property(\"success\");\r",
							"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property(\"message\");\r",
							"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property(\"data\");\r",
							"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property(\"pagination\");\r",
							"});\r",
							"\r",
							"\r",
							"/* CASE 1: No events found (data = null) */\r",
							"\r",
							"if (response.data === null) {\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Success flag should be false when no data\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.success).to.eql(false);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Pagination should be null\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.pagination).to.eql(null);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"}\r",
							"\r",
							"\r",
							"/* CASE 2: Events exist */\r",
							"\r",
							"else {\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Success flag should be true when events exist\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.success).to.eql(true);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Data should be an array\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.data).to.be.an(\"array\");\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Event object structure is valid\", function () {\r",
							"\r",
							"        let event = response.data[0];\r",
							"\r",
							"        pm.expect(event).to.have.property(\"event_id\");\r",
							"        pm.expect(event).to.have.property(\"category_name\");\r",
							"        pm.expect(event).to.have.property(\"event_title\");\r",
							"        pm.expect(event).to.have.property(\"event_description\");\r",
							"        pm.expect(event).to.have.property(\"claimed_status\");\r",
							"\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"All events should be unclaimed\", function () {\r",
							"\r",
							"        response.data.forEach(event => {\r",
							"            pm.expect(event.claimed_status).to.eql(0);\r",
							"        });\r",
							"\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"}"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {}
					}
				}
			],
			"protocolProfileBehavior": {
				"disableBodyPruning": true
			},
			"request": {
				"auth": {
					"type": "bearer",
					"bearer": [
						{
							"key": "token",
							"value": "{{token}}",
							"type": "string"
						}
					]
				},
				"method": "GET",
				"header": [],
				"body": {
					"mode": "raw",
					"raw": "",
					"options": {
						"raw": {
							"language": "json"
						}
					}
				},
				"url": {
					"raw": "{{moderator_api_url}}/events/1?page=1",
					"host": [
						"{{moderator_api_url}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"events",
						"1"
					],
					"query": [
						{
							"key": "page",
							"value": "1"
						}
					]
				},
				"description": "**Get All Events API**\n\nThis is a **GET API** used to retrieve all events for a specific region.\n\n**Endpoint**\n\n```\n{{moderator_api_url}}/events/{region_id}\n\n ```\n\n**Path Parameter**\n\n- `region_id` _(integer)_ – The ID of the region for which events need to be retrieved.\n    \n\n**Query Parameter**\n\n- `page` _(optional, integer)_ – Used for pagination to retrieve events page by page.\n    \n\n**Response**\n\nThe API returns a list of events associated with the specified region. Each event object contains the following details:\n\n- `event_id` – Unique identifier of the event\n    \n- `category` – The category to which the event belongs\n    \n- `event_title` – Title of the event\n    \n- `event_description` – Description of the event\n    \n- `claimed_status` – Indicates the claim status of the event\n    \n    - `0` → Event is **not claimed**\n        \n    - `1` → Event is **locked and claimed**"
			},
			"response": []
		},
		{
			"name": "Claim Event",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"let response = pm.response.json();\r",
							"\r",
							"/* Basic response validation */\r",
							"\r",
							"pm.test(\"Response has success field\", function () {\r",
							"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property(\"success\");\r",
							"});\r",
							"\r",
							"pm.test(\"Response has message field\", function () {\r",
							"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property(\"message\");\r",
							"});\r",
							"\r",
							"\r",
							"/* CASE 1: BODY MISSING */\r",
							"\r",
							"if (response.message === \"body is required\") {\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Status code should be 400\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.response.to.have.status(400);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Success flag should be false\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.success).to.eql(false);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Data should be null\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.data).to.eql(null);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"}\r",
							"\r",
							"\r",
							"/* CASE 2: INVALID EVENT */\r",
							"\r",
							"else if (response.message === \"No such event exists\") {\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Status code should be 200\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Success flag should be false\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.success).to.eql(false);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"\r",
							"}\r",
							"\r",
							"\r",
							"/* CASE 3: ALREADY CLAIMED EVENT */\r",
							"\r",
							"else if (response.message === \"Event already claimed.\") {\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Status code should be 200\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Success flag should be false\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.success).to.eql(false);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"\r",
							"}\r",
							"\r",
							"/* CASE 4: SUCCESSFUL CLAIM */\r",
							"\r",
							"else if (response.success === true && response.data !== null) {\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Status code should be 200\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Correct success message returned\", function () {\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.message).to.eql(\"Event successfully claimed\");\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.test(\"Response contains event data\", function () {\r",
							"\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property(\"event_id\");\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property(\"expire_time\");\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property(\"event_title\");\r",
							"        pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property(\"event_description\");\r",
							"\r",
							"    });\r",
							"\r",
							"    /* Save event id for acknowledge API */\r",
							"\r",
							"    pm.environment.set(\"event_id\", response.data.event_id);\r",
							"\r",
							"}\r",
							""
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {}
					}
				}
			],
			"request": {
				"auth": {
					"type": "bearer",
					"bearer": [
						{
							"key": "token",
							"value": "{{token}}",
							"type": "string"
						}
					]
				},
				"method": "POST",
				"header": [],
				"body": {
					"mode": "raw",
					"raw": "{\r\n    \"event_id\":104,\r\n    \"region_id\": 1,\r\n    \"moderator_id\": 1\r\n}",
					"options": {
						"raw": {
							"language": "json"
						}
					}
				},
				"url": {
					"raw": "{{moderator_api_url}}/claim",
					"host": [
						"{{moderator_api_url}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"claim"
					]
				},
				"description": "**Claim Event API**\n\nThis is a **POST API** used to claim an event for a specific moderator within a region. The request requires **token-based authorization**.\n\n**Authorization**\n\n- The request must include a valid **access token** in the authorization header to authenticate the moderator.\n    \n\n**Request Parameters**\n\n- `event_id` _(integer)_ – The unique identifier of the event to be claimed.\n    \n- `region_id` _(integer)_ – The region ID where the event belongs.\n    \n- `moderator_id` _(integer)_ – The ID of the moderator claiming the event.\n    \n\n**Functionality**\n\nWhen a moderator claims an event:\n\n- The `claimed_status` of the event is updated to **1**, indicating that the event has been **locked and claimed**.\n    \n- An **expiry date** is created and stored in the **assignment table** for that event.\n    \n- The **expiry date** is also returned in the API response.\n    \n\n**Response**\n\n- On successful claim, the API returns the **event details along with the expiry date**.\n    \n- If the event has already been claimed, the API returns the following message:\n    \n\n`Event already claimed`"
			},
			"response": []
		},
